# peekdiff environment
#
# Public repos need NOTHING here — the /api/diff proxy works unauthenticated.
# Auth is only required to view PRIVATE repositories.
#
# ⚠️ NEVER put real secrets in this file — it is committed. Copy it to
#    .env.local (gitignored) and fill in real values there.
#
# Choose ONE auth mode:
#
# (A) OAuth App — RECOMMENDED for personal use. One "Login with GitHub" grants
#     access to EVERY repo you can access (owner or contributor), no per-repo
#     install. Register: Settings -> Developer settings -> OAuth Apps -> New.
#     Takes precedence over the GitHub App below when both are set.
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# (B) GitHub App — least privilege; only sees repos the app is installed on.
#     Register: Settings -> Developer settings -> GitHub Apps.
GITHUB_APP_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_APP_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Optional: the GitHub App's URL slug, used to build an "install" link later.
# GITHUB_APP_SLUG=peekdiff
